Array : 
-------
1. Array is a non-primitive datatype
2. Array is a collection of homogenous as well as heterogenous data elements.
3. Array works on the concept of indexing.
4. Array indexing always starts from zero because it follows number system.
5. Prerequisite for array allocation is base address.
6. Array works on contigeous memory allocation.
7. Array elements shares same name but differentiable by there indexing.
8. Types of Array : 
    a. One Dimensional array (1d array)
    b. Two Dimensional array (2d array)
    c. Multi Dimensional array
There is also a special type of 2d array we have, which is known as jagged array.
9. In JavaScript we define array by square brackets like [].
10. Array can hold primitive data elements as well as object references.
11. We can also create array of objects just like number array, string array or mixed type array.


     0    1   2   3   4   <---------indexing
    _____________________
    | 2 | 4 | 5 | 8 | 8 |
    _____________________
  arr[0] arr[1] ....arr[4]   